# Portfolio Project Conventions

## Stack
- Next.js 15+ App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4
- All pages live in `src/app/`, components in `src/components/`

## Component Rules
- Functional components only, named exports unless it's a page/layout
- Props interfaces defined inline above the component
- Use `@/` alias for all imports (never relative `../../`)

## Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Use `text-foreground/70` opacity syntax for muted text
- Responsive: mobile-first, use `md:` and `lg:` breakpoints

## Content
- All site data (projects, skills) lives in `src/content/*.ts` as typed arrays
- Never hardcode content directly in components

## File Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Utilities/hooks: `camelCase.ts`
- Pages/layouts: lowercase `page.tsx` / `layout.tsx` (Next.js convention)
